        "text": "# Expert Recommendations for High Blood Pressure\n\n## Lifestyle Changes (First-line approach)\n\n**Diet:**\n- Follow the DASH diet (rich in fruits, vegetables, whole grains, lean proteins)\n- Reduce sodium to less than 2,300 mg/day (ideally 1,500 mg)\n- Limit alcohol consumption\n- Increase potassium intake (from foods like bananas, spinach)\n\n**Physical Activity:**\n- At least 150 minutes of moderate exercise weekly\n- Activities like brisk walking, swimming, cycling\n\n**Weight Management:**\n- Lose weight if overweight (even 5-10 lbs can help)\n- Maintain healthy BMI\n\n**Stress Reduction:**\n- Practice relaxation techniques\n- Adequate sleep (7-9 hours)\n- Meditation or deep breathing exercises\n\n**Quit Smoking:**\n- Smoking cessation significantly reduces cardiovascular risk\n\n## Medication\n\nWhen lifestyle changes aren't enough, doctors may prescribe:\n- Diuretics\n- ACE inhibitors\n- ARBs (Angiotensin II receptor blockers)\n- Calcium channel blockers\n- Beta-blockers\n\n## Monitoring\n\n- Regular blood pressure checks at home\n- Routine medical appointments\n- Track readings to share with your doctor\n\n**Important:** Always consult with your healthcare provider for personalized advice, as treatment varies based on individual health factors, severity, and other conditions.",
        "html": "<h1>Expert Recommendations for High Blood Pressure</h1>\n<h2>Lifestyle Changes (First-line approach)</h2>\n<p><strong>Diet:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Follow the DASH diet (rich in fruits, vegetables, whole grains, lean proteins)</li>\n<li>Reduce sodium to less than 2,300 mg/day (ideally 1,500 mg)</li>\n<li>Limit alcohol consumption</li>\n<li>Increase potassium intake (from foods like bananas, spinach)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Physical Activity:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>At least 150 minutes of moderate exercise weekly</li>\n<li>Activities like brisk walking, swimming, cycling</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Weight Management:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Lose weight if overweight (even 5-10 lbs can help)</li>\n<li>Maintain healthy BMI</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Stress Reduction:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Practice relaxation techniques</li>\n<li>Adequate sleep (7-9 hours)</li>\n<li>Meditation or deep breathing exercises</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Quit Smoking:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Smoking cessation significantly reduces cardiovascular risk</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Medication</h2>\n<p>When lifestyle changes aren&#39;t enough, doctors may prescribe:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Diuretics</li>\n<li>ACE inhibitors</li>\n<li>ARBs (Angiotensin II receptor blockers)</li>\n<li>Calcium channel blockers</li>\n<li>Beta-blockers</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Monitoring</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Regular blood pressure checks at home</li>\n<li>Routine medical appointments</li>\n<li>Track readings to share with your doctor</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Important:</strong> Always consult with your healthcare provider for personalized advice, as treatment varies based on individual health factors, severity, and other conditions.</p>\n"
